==Latin==
====Etymology====
From Latin '''[[forma]]''' ("form", "shape") + the adjective suffix '''[[-osus]]''' ("full of").

===Adjective===
'''formosa''' {{f}}

# [[beautiful]]; feminine singular nominative and ablative. The masculine nominative is '''[[formosus]]'''.


